name: graph
raw_recipe:
{% set name = "graph" %}
{% set version = "1.11" %}
{% set sha256 = "00432f3007b4cb2a8d6f2e021fd5625a79e307d6532971719ca6ab81dd0ae752" %}

package:
  name: {{ name|lower }}
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: {{ name }}-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://github.com/bjoern-andres/graph/archive/v{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

  patches:
    - hdf5_fixes.diff
    - install_fixes.diff
    - msvc_fixes.diff

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true        # [win32 or (win and py2k) and py36]
  features:
    - vc14          # [win and py>=35]

requirements:
  build:
    - python                  # [win]
    - toolchain
    - cmake
    - hdf5 1.8.17|1.8.17.*
  run:
    - hdf5 1.8.17|1.8.17.*

test:
  commands:
    - test -f $PREFIX/include/andres/graph/graph.hxx                  # [unix]
    - if not exist %LIBRARY_INC%\\andres\\graph\\graph.hxx exit 1     # [win]

about:
  home: http://www.andres.sc/graph.html
  license: BSD 3-clause
  license_family: BSD
  summary: 'Graphs and Graph Algorithms in C++, including Minimum Cost (Lifted) Multicuts'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - bluescarni

about.summary: Graphs and Graph Algorithms in C++, including Minimum Cost (Lifted) Multicuts
